'''Miwa Shrine''' (美和神社, *Miwa Jinja*) is a {{nihongo|Shinto shrine|神社}} located in Miyamoto-chō, Kiryu City, Gunma Prefecture, Japan. It is listed as a minor {{nihongo|Shikinaisha|式内社}} and was formerly ranked as a {{nihongo|Gōsha|郷社}} under the old shrine ranking system.

==Overview==
Miwa Shrine enshrines {{nihongo|Ōmononushi Kushi-mika-tama-no-Mikoto|大物主櫛甕玉命}} and {{nihongo|Takehayasusanoo-no-Mikoto|武速須佐之男命}}. It is situated at the southeastern foot of Mount Agatsuma in Kiryu, facing Yamate-dori Avenue. The shrine is known for hosting performances of {{nihongo|Kagura|神楽}} and taiko drumming during the annual {{nihongo|Kiryu Ebisu Festival|桐生ゑびす講}} held from November 19–20. A mikoshi (portable shrine) storehouse for the {{nihongo|Kiryu Yagibushi Festival|桐生八木節まつり}} is located adjacent to the worship hall.

==History==
Miwa Shrine is traditionally said to have been established during the reign of Emperor Sujin, with its deity transferred from Mount Miwa in Yamato Province. It was officially recognized as a shrine in 796 (Enryaku 15) alongside {{nihongo|Kamo Shrine|賀茂神社}}. In 880 (Gangyō 4), it was awarded the rank of Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade, alongside other shrines such as {{nihongo|Kamo Shrine|賀茂神社}}, {{nihongo|Kohachisu Shrine|甲波宿禰社}}, and {{nihongo|Oiwai Shrine|小祝社}}.

The shrine was referred to as "Conferred First Rank Miwa Daimyōjin" in the {{nihongo|Kōzuke no Kuni Jinmyōchō|上野国神名帳}}. Unfortunately, it lost many of its historical records and treasures in a fire during the Tenshō era.

Miwa Shrine was originally affiliated with {{nihongo|Enman-ji Temple|円満寺}}, and both were managed by the Kojima family during the Edo period. It was designated as a Gōsha in 1872 (Meiji 5) and merged with the former {{nihongo|Yasaka Shrine|八坂神社}} in 1908 (Meiji 41).

==Sub-Shrines==
* '''Yasaka Shrine''' – Former village shrine, merged in 1908
* '''Yagokoro-omoikane Shrine''' – Former precinct shrine of Yasaka Shrine
* '''Hata Shrine''' – Former precinct shrine of Yasaka Shrine
* '''Ichigami Shrine (Horinwa Gongen)''' – Former precinct shrine of Yasaka Shrine
* '''Matsuo Shrine'''
* '''Kotohira Shrine'''
* '''Nishinomiya Shrine'''

==Nearby Sites==
* {{nihongo|Kiryu-ga-oka Park|桐生が岡公園}}
* {{nihongo|Kiryu City Kita Elementary School|桐生市立北小学校}}

==References==
* {{Cite book |title=桐生市史 (Kiryu City History) |year=1958 |publisher=桐生市史刊行委員会 |editor=桐生市史編纂委員会}}
* {{Cite book |title=桐生市史 別巻 (Kiryu City History - Supplement) |year=1971 |publisher=桐生市役所 |editor=桐生市史別巻編集委員会}}

