== Cultural Events ==

The shrine is the center of the {{ill|Kiryu Ebisu Festival|ja|桐生ゑびす講|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiryu Ebisu Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 桐生西宮神社|1=Kiryū nishinomiya-jinja|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11537354}}, held annually from November 19 to 20. It features Kagura dances and taiko drum performances. Additionally, the shrine is involved in the {{ill|Kiryu Yagibushi Festival|ja|桐生八木節まつり|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiryu Yagibushi Festival|qq=|1=Kiryū Yagibushi festival|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11537271}}, where its mikoshi (portable shrine) is stored in an adjacent warehouse.

